_From [tobias.w...@gmail.com](https://code.google.com/u/113866277779216050036/) on December 18, 2010 13:37:40_

If I have a texture which applies to one sprite only, it would be useful if I can assign the file directly without the seperate declaration of a texture.

Also it would be useful if I could omit the texture width and height (the original size of the image will then be used).

Both can be done with a few new lines in Sprite.java:

import com.badlogic.gdx.graphics.Texture.TextureFilter;
import com.badlogic.gdx.graphics.Texture.TextureWrap;

public Sprite (String texture, TextureFilter minFilter, TextureFilter magFilter, TextureWrap uWrap, TextureWrap vWrap) {
    this(texture, minFilter, magFilter, uWrap, vWrap, 0, 0, 0, 0);
}

public Sprite (String texture, TextureFilter minFilter, TextureFilter magFilter, TextureWrap uWrap, TextureWrap vWrap, int srcWidth, int srcHeight) {
    this(texture, minFilter, magFilter, uWrap, vWrap, 0, 0, srcWidth, srcHeight);
}

public Sprite (String texture, TextureFilter minFilter, TextureFilter magFilter, TextureWrap uWrap, TextureWrap vWrap, int srcX, int srcY, int srcWidth, int srcHeight) {
    this.texture=Gdx.graphics.newTexture( Gdx.files.getFileHandle( texture, FileType.Internal), minFilter, magFilter, uWrap, vWrap);
    if(srcWidth==0) srcWidth=this.texture.getWidth();
    if(srcHeight==0) srcHeight=this.texture.getHeight();
    setRegion(srcX, srcY, srcWidth, srcHeight);
    setColor(1, 1, 1, 1);
    setSize(Math.abs(srcWidth), Math.abs(srcHeight));
    setOrigin(width / 2, height / 2);
}

and a modification of the normal/old constructor (to allow the auto width/height):

public Sprite (Texture texture, int srcX, int srcY, int srcWidth, int srcHeight) {
    if (texture == null) throw new IllegalArgumentException("texture cannot be null.");
    this.texture = texture;
    if(srcWidth==0) srcWidth=this.texture.getWidth();
    if(srcHeight==0) srcHeight=this.texture.getHeight();
...

