_From [tobias.w...@gmail.com](https://code.google.com/u/113866277779216050036/) on December 17, 2010 18:45:55_

Maybe it is working as intended, but when I write a font to a spritebatch, the master blending color seems to change (to the font color).

To prevent this I have to use:
        Color col=batch.getColor();
        font.draw(batch, "foo", x, y);
        batch.setColor(col);

I think it would be better when the font uses "his" color but doesn't touch the master blending color of the spriteBatch.

This example illustrates the problem:
    BitmapFont font;
    font.setColor(Color.BLACK);
    [...]
    spriteBatch.setColor(1.0f,1.0f,1.0f,1.0f);
    pinfo.render(); // playerinfo, renders a sprite and a text via font
    otherobject.render(); // I see a black texture (because the blending has changed "silently")

