_From [tobias.w...@gmail.com](https://code.google.com/u/113866277779216050036/) on December 14, 2010 09:57:22_

To make some things easier, I tried to set a camera which centers on 0,0 and with a width of 1024 pixels:
spriteBatch.getProjectionMatrix().setToOrtho2D(-512, -512, 1024, 1024);

But this didn't work.
I checked the libgfx-source and found:

public Matrix4 setToOrtho2D (float x, float y, float width, float height) {
    setToOrtho(0, width, 0, height, 0, 1);
    return this;
}

but this seems incorrect. I changed it to:
    setToOrtho(x, x+width, y, y+height, 0, 1);
and now it works correctly.

Version: latest from trunk.

_Original issue: http://code.google.com/p/libgdx/issues/detail?id=75_

_From [lf3th...@gmail.com](https://code.google.com/u/114271525039123168784/) on November 15, 2010 11:22:04_

Instead of:
out.x = x / child.scaleX - (child.x - child.originX);
out.y = x / child.scaleY - (child.y - child.originY);
(Note the "x" on the second line.)

It should be:
out.x = (x - child.x - child.originX) / child.scaleX + child.originX;
out.y = (y - child.y - child.originY) / child.scaleY + child.originY;

